		<li class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1 clearfix" id="comment-56688">
		<div id="div-comment-56688" class="clearfix comment-container">
		<div class="comment-author vcard">
		<img alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/ae94ced29845730503430bcb3fa688d1?s=55&amp;d=http%3A%2F%2F0.gravatar.com%2Favatar%2Fad516503a11cd5ca435acc9bb6523536%3Fs%3D55&amp;r=G' class='avatar avatar-55 photo' height='55' width='55' />		<span class="authorname">TellyGunge</span>
		</div>
				<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata">
		<a href="http://blog.ninapaley.com/2013/01/18/ahimsa-sita-sings-the-blues-now-cc-0-public-domain/comment-page-1/#comment-56688">
		January 20, 2013 at 6:28 am</a>
        		 
		</div>
		<p>First of all Nina, congratulations and thank you for your fantastic movie.</p>
<p>I believe in copyleft (for as long as copyright exists) and use CC-BY-SA for my writings. I see it not just as a means of preserving freedom in the work, but of spreading the idea of free culture. I&#8217;m sorry it didn&#8217;t work out for you. </p>
<p>It&#8217;s also sad that the proprietary music licenses will continue to limit the film&#8217;s freedom more than any Creative Commons license ever could.</p>
<p>I join you in looking forward to the day when copyleft becomes redundant, and the public domain is all that exists.</p>
		</div>
